### LGF_MergeBytesToWord Algorithm Process Description  

#### Core Logic Flow  
1. **Memory Structure Preparation**  
   - Create a temporary word variable (16-bit storage space), defaulting to little-endian storage mode  

2. **Byte Data Assembly**  
   - Directly write input byte1 to the high 8 bits of the temporary word (corresponding to address %W0.%B1)  
   - Directly write input byte0 to the low 8 bits of the temporary word (corresponding to address %W0.%B0)  

3. **Output Processing**  
   - Assign the fully assembled temporary word as the function return value  
   - Set ENO (Enable Output) to True